column15: Note that PRE priced a rev of the design with different racking, inverters, and modules than the other bidders.  Most importantly, they assumed HailPro racking and a 60 degree stow angle in their pricing, which is a more expensive product and requires more robust foundation design.

Note that PRE priced an HV general arrangement with a larger pad area (additional 2 acres) and additional bus structure than the other bidders.  MAM, BLT, and MT priced this earlier PV substation design on an indicative basis.
PRE bid a significantly more compressed schedule, solving for end of year 2027 COD.
